name: Angelica Morrone
title: Venture Capital Investor, Keynote Speaker, A&J Powerful Pills, Funding Strategist, Board member, Published Author
headline:
I accelerate impact investments.  I help impactful startups go from invisible to investible, after which I invest in them or connect them with the most successful and knowledgeable angel investors for winning partnerships!

The spark that ignited my interest in startups was formed during 27 incredible years in the investment world at the helm of my asset management company, co-founded in 1997.  

The secret to being successful in any field is the ability to understand what motivates people and to inspire them to reach their highest potential.  

My professional foundations are built on strong core values and proven business tenets, and a leadership philosophy centered around people.  

My mission is to ensure that all startups have a fair chance at success by applying proven methodologies and that angel investors are able to de-risk their portfolio thanks to the methodologies applied.  In 2020, my book, Invisible to Investible reached Amazon best seller.

name: Erin Saign
title: Partnerships Manager, Creators at Meta (formerly Facebook)
headline: As a seasoned professional in the dynamic landscape of gaming, lifestyle, and digital entertainment, I am a Senior Partnerships Manager at Meta. In my current role since September 2019, I have expertly overseen a diverse portfolio of top creators across Meta's family of apps, including Facebook, Instagram, and Threads. Among my notable achievements, I designed and launched the Third Party Partners program, fostering partnerships with leading agencies focused on traditional and gaming creators. I successfully led the Threads beta program and product launch across all gaming and initiated the Black Gaming Creator Program to promote diversity, equity, and inclusion within the gaming community. My strategic prowess extends to driving product adoption across Meta ecosystems and collaborating cross-functionally with various teams. Prior to my role at Meta, I held a Senior Manager position at Machinima/Fullscreen (a subdivision of Warner Bros), where I managed influencers and played a key role in brand awareness and campaign execution. With a career spanning talent management, digital strategy, and analytics, I have consistently demonstrated my ability to innovate and elevate brands in the digital space.
